track_notes: Limited parking along this lane. I was dropped off. Follow public right of way through farm land, very boggy in places. Emerge onto hillside through small gate, after that it is easy going up hill to the summit.

Park off the A499 on the old road. Find the track at SH38574678, up the lane and diverting across field north of cottage. Zig-zag up the hill past the Tan-y-graig granite quarry.

Over the bwlch pick up Geralds track near Fron-heulog, turning left through rusty gate. Head straight up towards the summit.

Gaining the summit proper means scrambling over lots of slippery boulders.

Park at a sizeable layby at SH 4372 4779.  Walk south along road for 300m, to the stone step stile on the corner.  Follow the clear track up the hillside, marked with poles, through several gateways. It starts steeply, until it levels at the shoulder.  Continue flatish across fields on the obvious paths, with stiles on stone walls.  
At SH 4162 4663 the route is hemmed in by parallel walls for 200m.  It is very muddy due to animal traffic.  As soon as you get to the end of this section it opens out onto drier grass.  Bear right on a smaller track, to soon start the climb with a wall to your right.
Near the top, skirt left to easily avoid a boulder field, before turning right along the top wall to a large cairn and gap in the wall.  
Continue to main summit via a small drop in height.  Summit area is a massive area of large boulders.  Pick your own route (north side a bit easier in my opinion) On this occassion I stopped short of the summit due to very slippery/windy conditions.
